2020-05-17

Quality control of the Swedish lexicon. Verbs in particular:

Irregular verbs from IrregSwe:

- write_VCSE =  (mkV "skriva")  --> I.skriva_V

Regular verbs that end with "er" in present tense can be given with mkN:

- decide_VCSE =  (mkV "bestämma")  --> mkV "bestämmer"

mkV with two arguments should be avoided; if used, the second argument is the past tense

  articulate_VCSE =  (mkV "artikulera" "artikulerar") --> mkV "artikulera" "artikulerade"
                                        BUT BETTER:       mkV "artikulera"
					EVEN BETTER:      artikulera_V

What is this? Is it a verb at all? (even in English?)

- username_VCSE =  (mkV "användarnamn") ;

Those "verbs" that don't end with "a" are probably not verbs.

The best solution: use morphodict/MorphoDictSwe entries whenever possible!

